content.description: This is a gem of an arete climb in the 11c range at deep creek. Several big moves give way to a mantle onto a no hands rest. Ledge pulling to the anchors. can’t beat the position on the wall and the view into the creek side area.
content.location: To the right of back in the saddle and left of murder hornet.

climbs.name: Murder hornet
climbs.fa: Cody averbeck, Dave Wilson, Laban swafford

content.description: Climb a fun corner and pull over/mantle onto a ledge. Continue on jugs to a thin upper face with crimps and edges.  Good route at creek side
content.protection: Bolts. Carabiners on hangers at top.
content.location: To the right of shenanigans in the obtuse corner.

content.description: Work your way up the vertical wall using ledges and laybacks.
content.location: In Creekside area, 10 to 15 minute hike upstream from main wall (cairn marking beginning of trail from main wall. on rocky ledge just past the huge slab boulder.

content.description: Powerful start on sandy ledges to fun moves on more ledges. Rest then pull roof and crux to anchors.
content.location: Leftmost route, just before stream. Shares first bolt w Dry Time(11a)

content.description: Start on ledge. Dark colored, left facing dihedral. Climb dihedral and arete to crevice.
content.location: Left facing dark colored dihedral up on ledge as your coming down trail to the creek.

content.description: Fun and well-protected climbing leads to a creative crux up high.
content.location: Walk climber's left out of the Stallion Cave and up the hill. At the top of the hill near a large boulder, two climbs go up the face. Airnet is the one on the right.

content.description: AM shade/PM sun. Vertical to gently overhung tech face, with crisp edges and good rock.
